  "prompt": "Who discovered Avogadro's number?",
  "response": "Avogadro's number, which represents the number of particles (atoms, molecules, or ions) in one mole of a substance, was not directly discovered by Amedeo Avogadro. While Avogadro proposed the hypothesis that equal volumes of gases at the same temperature and pressure contain the same number of molecules, the actual numerical value of Avogadro's number was determined much later by Jean Perrin in the early 20th century. Perrin experimentally verified the number through multiple methods in 1909, for which he was awarded the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1926.",
